			<item>
				<title>Dragonball Z Budokai 3 - 22 years old password algorithm finally reversed</title>
				<link>http://localhost:1313/blog/dbzb3-rev/</link>
				<pubDate>Sat, 09 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
				<guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/dbzb3-rev/</guid>
				<description>&lt;p&gt;Dragon Ball Z Budokai 3 is a PlayStation 2 video game released in 2004. The best Dragon Ball game ever, if you ask me :)&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;After spending countless hours playing it as a kid, and after recently replaying it again, I decided to reverse engineer the game to understand how the character password mechanic works.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The goal of this little project is to understand how the game turns a password into a character, and how it validates it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
			</item>
